title: Birth rate
subtitle: The number of live births occurring during the year, per 1,000 people. ${projection__subtitle}

title: ${sex__title_prefix} deaths ${age_group__title_suffix}
subtitle: ${projection__subtitle}

title: ${sex__title_prefix} deaths ${age_group__title_suffix}
subtitle: ${projection__subtitle}

title: Death rate
subtitle: The number of deaths occurring during the year, per 1,000 people. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Number of ${sex__title_prefix} child deaths
subtitle: The number of children who die before reaching the age of 5. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Child mortality rate
subtitle: The share of children who die before reaching the age of 5. ${projection__subtitle}
note: This is the probability of a child born in a specific year or period dying before reaching the age of 5, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of that period. This is given as the share of live births.

title: Number of ${sex__title_prefix} infant deaths
subtitle: The number of newborns who die before reaching the age of one. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Infant mortality rate
subtitle: The share of newborns who die before reaching the age of one. ${projection__subtitle}
note: This is the probability of a child born in a specific year or period dying before reaching the age of 1, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of that period. This is given as the share of live births.

title: Fertility rate: children per woman
subtitle: ${projection__subtitle}
note: The total fertility rate is the number of children that would be born to a woman if she were to live to the end of her child-bearing years and give birth to children at the current age-specific fertility rates.

title: Fertility rate ${age_group__title_suffix}
subtitle: This rate measures the number of live births ${age_group__title_suffix} per 1,000 women in that age group. ${projection__subtitle}
_age_group: mothers_15_19 mothers_20_24 mothers_25_29 mothers_30_34 mothers_35_39 mothers_40_44 mothers_45_49

title: Natural population growth rate
subtitle: The natural growth rate is the population change determined by births and deaths. Migration flows are not taken into account. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Population growth rate
subtitle: The growth rate is the population change determined by births, deaths, and migration flows. ${projection__subtitle}

title: ${sex__title_prefix} life expectancy at birth
subtitle: ${projection__subtitle}
note: Shown is the ‘period life expectancy’ at birth. This is the average number of years a newborn would live if age-specific mortality rates in the current year were to stay the same throughout its life.

title: ${sex__title_prefix} life expectancy ${age_group__title_suffix}
subtitle: Life expectancy for individuals who have reached age ${age_group__csv_slug}. Estimates are expressed as the expected age at death, not as years left to live. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Net migration
subtitle: The total number of immigrants (people moving into a given country) minus the number of emigrants (people moving out of the country). ${projection__subtitle}

title: Net migration rate
subtitle: The total number of immigrants (people moving into a given country) minus the number of emigrants (people moving out of the country), per 1,000 people in the population. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Sex ratio
subtitle: ​​The number of male population per 100 female population. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Sex ratio at birth
subtitle: ​​The number of male births per 100 female births. Biological birth ratios are slightly male-biased, with an expected ratio of 105 male births per 100 female births. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Sex ratio ${age_group__title_suffix}
subtitle: The number of male individuals per 100 female individuals, ${age_group__title_suffix}. ${projection__subtitle}

title: Total ${sex__title_prefix} dependency ratio
subtitle: The ratio of the young ${sex__title_prefix} population (under age 15) and elderly population (aged 65 and over) to the working-age ${sex__title_prefix} population (aged 15 to 64). ${projection__subtitle}

title: ${sex__title_prefix} youth dependency ratio
subtitle: The ratio of the young ${sex__title_prefix} population (under age 15) to the working-age ${sex__title_prefix} population (aged 15 to 64). ${projection__subtitle}

title: ${sex__title_prefix} old-age dependency ratio
subtitle: The ratio of the elderly ${sex__title_prefix} population (aged 65 and over) to the working-age ${sex__title_prefix} population (aged 15 to 64). ${projection__subtitle}

title: Median age
subtitle: The median age divides the population into two parts of equal size; that is, there are as many people with ages above the median age as there are with ages below. ${projection__subtitle}
